text: Ask-wee-da-eed is a Native American mythological figure of the Algonquian Abenaki people. The figure is a shaman who is half-snake, half-man. He forces humans to find the materials with which he would cook them, before he was killed by Moosbas.http://www.mandrake- press.co.uk/Main_article/native_american_mythology.html Mandrake Article ==References== Category:Abenaki legendary creatures
title: Ato-sees
